# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
# Place this file in the public/ directory of your Astro project.
# Syntax: /source  /destination  [status_code]
# Default status code is 301 (permanent redirect) if omitted.

# ─── TRAILING-SLASH NORMALISATION ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Astro generates URLs without trailing slashes by default (trailingSlash: 'never').
# These rules prevent duplicate-content indexing. Add one line per page
# if you ever publish at a path that Google might crawl with a trailing slash.
# Example:
# /articles/  /articles  301

# ─── BAMSYAR.PAGES.DEV → CUSTOM DOMAIN ──────────────────────────────────────
# After your custom domain is live, redirect the .pages.dev subdomain to avoid
# duplicate indexing. Cloudflare does not do this automatically.
# Uncomment the line below only after your custom domain is confirmed working.
# https://bamsyar.pages.dev/*  https://yourdomain.com/:splat  301

# ─── LEGACY / RENAMED PATHS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Add redirects here if you rename or move articles after publishing.
# Never delete a published URL — redirect it. Google Scholar and arXiv
# citation links are permanent once indexed.
# Example:
# /articles/h-bar-model  /articles/h-bar-model-schema-coherence-ai-training  301

# ─── 404 FALLBACK ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare Pages uses your dist/404.html automatically if it exists.
# No explicit redirect needed here — Astro generates it from src/pages/404.astro.
